class Colors:

    def __getitem__(self, item):
        pass
class Side:

    def __init__(self):
        self.colors = Colors()
with patch.object(Cube, 'get_side', return_value=Side()) as mock_method:
    runtime = CubeRuntime(Cube((3, 3, 3)), Orientation(), lambda action:
        None, lambda : None)
    runtime.get_color(side, 0, 0)
    mock_method.assert_called_once_with(orientation)
pytest.mark.parametrize('side, orientation', [(Side.FRONT, Orientation(Side
    .FRONT, Side.TOP)), (Side.LEFT, Orientation(Side.LEFT, Side.TOP)), (
    Side.RIGHT, Orientation(Side.RIGHT, Side.TOP)), (Side.BACK, Orientation
    (Side.BACK, Side.TOP)), (Side.TOP, Orientation(Side.TOP, Side.BACK)), (
    Side.BOTTOM, Orientation(Side.BOTTOM, Side.FRONT))])
